de.oaam.model.oaam.library

Interface ResourceTypeModifierReference

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourceTypeModifierReferenceImpl

    public interface ResourceTypeModifierReference
extends OaamBaseElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Resource Type Modifier Reference'. The modifier definition relates modifier types and modifier levels to modifiers that can be assigned to resource types.

    The following features are supported:

    • Type
    • Allowed Levels
    See Also:
    LibraryPackage.getResourceTypeModifierReference()

      • getType

        ResourceTypeModifier getType()
        Returns the value of the 'Type' reference. The modifier type. There can be more than one modifier definitions for one type, e.g. if different levels are allowed

        the value of the 'Type' reference.

      • getAllowedLevels

        org.eclipse.emf.common.util.EList<ResourceTypeModifierLevel> getAllowedLevels()
        Returns the value of the 'Allowed Levels' reference list. The list contents are of type ResourceTypeModifierLevel. A list of modifier levels allowed for this modifier. For instance a lightning protection modifier could allow L1,L2,L4,L5,L6,L8.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Allowed Levels' reference list.
        See Also:
        LibraryPackage.getResourceTypeModifierReference_AllowedLevels()
